Ingredients: - 1 cup of peanut butter (natural, no added sugar) - 1/2 cup of honey or maple syrup - 2 cups of oat flakes - 1 cup of peanuts (whole or chopped) - 1/2 cup of chocolate chips or chunks (preferably dark or semi-sweet) - 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract - A pinch of salt (optional)
Steps: 1. In a saucepan over medium heat, warm the peanut butter and honey... 2. Remove the mixture from heat and add the oat flakes, peanuts... 3. Mix everything until all ingredients are fully combined... 4. In a square or rectangular mold, previously lined with parchment paper... 5. Refrigerate the mixture for at least 2-3 hours... 6. Once firm, remove the mixture from the mold and cut it into desired-sized bars...
