// Chocolate and Nut Brownies
Chocolate and Nut Brownies
200g of dark chocolate (minimum 70% cocoa) 150g of unsalted butter 200g of sugar 100g of chopped nuts
Preheat the oven to 180°C and prepare a square mold. Melt the chocolate and butter in a double boiler. In a bowl, beat the eggs with the sugar until a mixture is obtained. Incorporate the chocolate and butter mixture into the bowl.
// Fruit Salad with Honey and Lemon
2 bananas 1 apple 1 pear 1 cup of strawberries 1 cup of grapes 2 tablespoons of honey
Peel and cut all the fruits into small pieces. Mix the fruits in a large bowl. Add the honey and gently mix to coat the fruits. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.
// Oat and Raisin Cookies
1 cup of oat flour 1/2 cup of brown sugar 1/2 cup of melted butter 1 egg 1 teaspoon of vanilla essence 1/2 cup of raisins
Steps: Preheat the oven to 180°C. In a large bowl, mix oat flour, brown sugar, melted butter, egg, and vanilla essence. Add the raisins to the mixture and stir until evenly distributed. Shape the dough into balls and place them on a baking tray. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool and enjoy your oat and raisin cookies.
// Nutty Cookies
1 cup of flour 1/2 cup of melted butter 1/2 cup of sugar 1 egg 1 cup of chopped nuts (walnuts, almonds, hazelnuts, etc.)
Steps: Preheat the oven to 180°C. In a large bowl, mix the flour, melted butter, sugar, and egg until obtaining a homogeneous dough. Add the chopped nuts to the dough and mix well. Shape small balls with the dough and place them on a baking tray. Bake for 12-15 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool and enjoy your nutty cookies.
200g of vanilla cookies 100g of melted butter 400g of condensed milk Juice of 4 lemons Zest of 2 lemons 100g of mixed nuts (walnuts, almonds, hazelnuts) 200ml of heavy cream
Steps: Crush the vanilla cookies and mix them with the melted butter. Cover the base of a removable mold with this mixture and refrigerate. In a bowl, mix the condensed milk, lemon juice, and lemon zest. Pour this mixture over the cookie base and refrigerate for 1 hour. Whip the heavy cream until soft peaks form. Spread it over the tart and decorate with the mixed nuts. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving and enjoy the lemon and nut tart.
// Vegan Chocolate Cake
2 cups of wheat flour 1 cup of sugar 1/2 cup of unsweetened cocoa powder 1 teaspoon of baking soda 1/2 teaspoon of salt 1/2 cup of vegetable oil 2 teaspoons of apple cider vinegar 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract 1 cup of water Vegan chocolate frosting Strawberries or red berries for decoration (optional)
Steps: Preheat the oven to 180°C and grease a cake pan. In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt. Add the vegetable oil, apple cider vinegar, vanilla extract, and water. Mix well until smooth and homogeneous. Pour the mixture into the prepared pan and bake for 30-35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Allow the cake to cool before applying the vegan chocolate frosting. Decorate with strawberries or red berries if desired.
1 cup oat flour 1/2 cup melted butter 1/2 cup sugar 1 egg Juice and zest of 2 lemons
Steps: Preheat the oven to 180°C (350°F). In a large bowl, mix oat flour, melted butter, sugar, egg, lemon juice, and lemon zest until you get a homogeneous dough. Form balls with the dough and place them on a baking sheet. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until golden. Let them cool and enjoy your lemon and oat cookies.
// Vegan Chocolate Mousse
200g vegan dark chocolate 1 cup almond milk 1 teaspoon vanilla extract 1 tablespoon coconut sugar (optional)
Steps: Melt the chocolate using a double boiler or microwave and let it cool. In a bowl, mix almond milk, vanilla extract, and coconut sugar (optional). Incorporate the melted chocolate into the previous mixture and stir well until you get a homogeneous texture. Refrigerate for at least 3 hours before serving. Serve and garnish with fresh fruits or nuts according to your preference.
// Lemon Mousse with Oat Base
1 cup oatmeal 1/2 cup almond milk Juice and zest of 3 lemons 3 tablespoons coconut sugar 1/2 cup coconut cream
Steps: Process the oatmeal until obtaining a fine flour. Mix oat flour with almond milk and form the base in individual molds. Refrigerate for 15 minutes. In a bowl, mix lemon juice and zest with coconut sugar. Add coconut cream to the previous mixture and beat until smooth and creamy. Pour the mixture over the oat base in the molds and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
// Lemon and Blueberry Muffins
1 3/4 cups wheat flour 1/2 cup sugar 2 teaspoons baking powder 1/2 teaspoon salt Zest of 2 lemons 1/2 cup vegetable oil 3/4 cup almond milk 2 tablespoons lemon juice 1 cup fresh blueberries
Steps: Preheat the oven to 190°C (375°F) and prepare muffin tins with liners. In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and lemon zest. In another bowl, combine vegetable oil, almond milk, and lemon juice. Add this mixture to the dry ingredients and mix until combined. Gently fold in the blueberries into the mixture. Pour the batter into the muffin tins and bake for 20-25 minutes or until golden. Let them cool before serving and enjoy your lemon and blueberry muffins.
